<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>☃️ M003 Extension — Build the Snow Golem (Beginner)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> 3D Snow Golem (x, y, z) · <strong>Course:</strong> 3D Coordinates · <strong>Level:</strong> Beginner (Extension, after Week 6) · <strong>Time:</strong> about 30 minutes</p>
<p>Build a standing snow golem in 3D — <strong>snow body</strong>, <strong>pumpkin head</strong>, <strong>coal buttons</strong>, <strong>stick arms</strong>. Every block needs <strong>three</strong> numbers <strong>(x, y, z)</strong>: x <strong>across</strong>, y <strong>up</strong>, z <strong>deeper</strong> (forward).</p>
<blockquote>
<p>🔴 Stand on your <strong>home spot</strong> (red block) every run. Move, and the golem moves too.</p>
<p>🎨 Snow = <strong>snow block</strong>. Head = <strong>carved pumpkin</strong>. Buttons + eyes = <strong>coal block</strong>. Arms = a <strong>brown block</strong> (oak log).</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read the code. Circle one word.</p>
<pre><code>place snow block at (3, 1, 1)
place snow block at (3, 2, 1)
place snow block at (3, 3, 1)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Only y changes. This snow tower is going... Circle one:</strong> across · up · deeper</p>
<pre><code>place snow block at (3, 3, 1)
place snow block at (3, 3, 2)
place snow block at (3, 3, 3)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Only z changes. Circle one:</strong> across · up · deeper</p>
<hr />
<h2>2 · Spot the Bug 🐛</h2>
<p>A coal button sits <strong>on the front</strong> of the body at (3, 4, 1). The code below has only <strong>two</strong> numbers, so it lands flat on the ground.</p>
<pre><code># broken
place coal block at (3, 4)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Fill the blank to fix it:</strong></p>
<pre><code>place coal block at (3, 4, __)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Which number fills the blank? Circle one:</strong> 1 · 3</p>
<p><strong>What was missing? Circle one:</strong> the z number · the color</p>
<hr />
<h2>3 · Show Your Work 📸🎥</h2>
<p>Look at the ☃️ snow golem in the world. Walk around it. See the pumpkin head up top, the coal buttons down the front, and the two arms poking out the sides.</p>
<p><strong>Build a small snow golem on your home spot.</strong> Keep it easy:</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Snow body:</strong> fill snow blocks from (2, 1, 1) up to (4, 5, 1) — a tall tower.</p>
<p><strong>Pumpkin head on top:</strong> fill carved pumpkin from (2, 6, 1) to (4, 7, 1).</p>
<p><strong>Two coal eyes on the head:</strong> coal block at (2, 7, 1) and (4, 7, 1).</p>
<p><strong>Two coal buttons on the body:</strong> coal block at (3, 4, 1) and (3, 2, 1).</p>
<p><strong>Two arms out the sides:</strong> a brown block at (1, 4, 1) and (5, 4, 1).</p>
<p>💡 Tip: the head goes <strong>up</strong> (bigger y). The arms poke <strong>out</strong> (x = 1 and x = 5). Everything shows on the <strong>front</strong> (z = 1).</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Record <strong>one video</strong> — one take, no stopping (a phone is fine). Show these in order:</p>
<p><strong>1 · Your code.</strong> Scroll through it. Say what each part does.</p>
<p><strong>2 · Your build.</strong> Point the camera at the golem. Name the parts.</p>
<p>Say these out loud, filling in the blanks:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Today I built ______.</p>
<p>I built it using this code: ______.</p>
<p>In this code I used ______.</p>
<p>The hardest part was ______.</p>
<p>That part was hard because ______.</p>
<p>The most fun part was ______.</p>
<p>Something new I learned was ______.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your <strong>one</strong> video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
